%% Sync Push-Pull Sequence Diagram
%% Device pushes local changes, then pulls remote changes

sequenceDiagram
    participant App as App (UseCase/Repo)
    participant Room as Room DB
    participant SE as SyncEngine
    participant SQ as SyncQueue
    participant SW as SyncWorker
    participant API as Cloud API
    participant PG as PostgreSQL

    Note over App,Room: 1. Local Write (always first)
    App->>Room: save(entity) with syncStatus=PENDING_UPLOAD
    App->>SE: notifyChange(entityType, entityId)
    SE->>SQ: enqueue(entityType, entityId, CREATE/UPDATE)

    Note over SW,API: 2. Push (Device -> Cloud)
    SW->>SQ: query all QUEUED entries
    SQ-->>SW: List of pending changes
    SW->>API: POST /api/sync/push { batch: [...] }
    API->>PG: validate & apply changes
    PG-->>API: accepted / conflict per item

    alt Accepted
        API-->>SW: { status: ACCEPTED, cloudVersion: N }
        SW->>Room: update syncStatus=SYNCED, syncVersion=N
        SW->>SQ: mark COMPLETED
    else Conflict
        API-->>SW: { status: CONFLICT, cloudData: {...} }
        SW->>Room: update syncStatus=CONFLICT
        SW->>SQ: mark FAILED (needs resolution)
    else Network Error
        SW->>SQ: increment retryCount, set nextRetryAt (backoff)
    end

    Note over SW,API: 3. Pull (Cloud -> Device)
    SW->>API: GET /api/sync/pull?since={lastSyncVersion}
    API->>PG: query changes since version
    PG-->>API: List of remote changes
    API-->>SW: { changes: [...], latestVersion: M }
    SW->>Room: apply remote changes (upsert)
    SW->>SW: update lastSyncVersion = M

    Note over SE,API: 4. Real-time (optional, SSE)
    API-->>SE: SSE event: new changes available
    SE->>SW: trigger immediate pull
